  Name: Dassault Rafale
  Information: The Dassault Rafale is a French twin-engine, canard-delta wing, 4.5-generation
    multirole fighter produced by Dassault Aviation. Designed for air superiority,
    strikes, and nuclear deterrence, it is operated by the French Air Force/Navy
    and exported to nine countries. It features high maneuverability, advanced sensors
    (AESA radar, SPECTRA EW suite), and can carry 9,500 kg of payload.
